node.title: Four-year-old twin sisters die in house fire near Byron Bay
node.alt: NSW police generic logo on uniform sleeve of policeman
node.description: Investigators are working to determine the cause of a fatal house fire in northern NSW which caused the death of twin sisters,Â aged four.
node.content:
["An investigation is underway after four-year-old twin girls died following a house fire near Byron Bay on the New South Wales north coast\u00a0early this morning.", "Police, paramedics and fire crews were called to the single-storey home at Goonengerry, which was part of a multiple-occupancy community, about 30 kilometres west of Byron Bay west about 4am.", "They performed CPR on both children, who had been reported as suffering from smoke inhalation, but the twins\u00a0were\u00a0unable to be revived.", "A woman at the scene is also being treated for shock.", "
Low-temperature fire
", "Initial reports indicate a candle that was left burning may have been the cause of the blaze.", "Detectives and fire investigators will work together to confirm the cause of the fire.", "The ABC understands it was a smouldering low-temperature fire which caused a lot of smoke but not much damage to the property.", "It's believed the twin girls were asleep and were unable to be woken after suffering smoke inhalation from smoke fumes.", "The ABC also understands the girls were staying with their father at the property.", "More to come."]
